{"title":"Sigil of tempest","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Sigil_of_tempest","type":"markdown","data":"**Sigil of tempest** is a [technique](/wiki/Technique \"Technique\") in [SLASH'EM](/wiki/SLASH%27EM \"SLASH'EM\"). When used, it creates 3x3 explosions around you centered in a 7x7 area (excluding the 3x3 area around you, so you will not be hit) instead of firing a [ray](/wiki/Ray \"Ray\"). This technique affects all ray-based spells except [finger of death](/wiki/Spellbook_of_finger_of_death \"Spellbook of finger of death\").\n\nWhen used with [sigil of control](/wiki/Sigil_of_control \"Sigil of control\"), the explosion can be controlled as if you cast [fireball](/wiki/Spellbook_of_fireball \"Spellbook of fireball\") or [cone of cold](/wiki/Spellbook_of_cone_of_cold \"Spellbook of cone of cold\") at [skilled](/wiki/Skilled \"Skilled\") level or above in vanilla [NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\").\n\nWhen used with [sigil of discharge](/wiki/Sigil_of_discharge \"Sigil of discharge\"), the number of explosions doubles.\n\n## Bugs\n\nMost ray-based spells in SLASH'EM, as well as [fireball](/wiki/Fireball \"Fireball\") explosion, use six-sided damage dice. It seems sigil of tempest explosions were supposed to deal (XL/4 + bonus)d6 damage[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1), however, due to what is probably a bug, they do only plain (XL/4 + bonus) damage[\\[2\\]](#cite_note-2), resulting in single digit damage in most cases, making the technique mostly useless.\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [zap.c in SLASH'EM 0.0.7E7F2, line 2273](/wiki/Source:SLASH%27EM_0.0.7E7F2/zap.c#line2273 \"Source:SLASH'EM 0.0.7E7F2/zap.c\")\n2. [↑](#cite_ref-2) cf. fireball code: [zap.c in SLASH'EM 0.0.7E7F2, line 4246](/wiki/Source:SLASH%27EM_0.0.7E7F2/zap.c#line4246 \"Source:SLASH'EM 0.0.7E7F2/zap.c\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Sigil of tempest - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.classNa